  "title": "Occupational Therapist",
  "description": "<p>-Performs overall Occupational Therapy Assessment and Treatment. Maintains optimum standards of Occupational Therapy care and practice.</p>\n<p>-Identify treatment planning, implementation, re-evaluation and discharge planningfor client.</p>\n<p>-Diverse presentations of physical and psychological conditions.</p>\n<p>-Undertakes all aspects of clinical duties as an autonomous practitioner, in delivery of health promotional activities.</p>\n<p>-Conversant with the Standard Operation PRocedures (SOPs) of the centre and is compliant with the requirements specified.</p>\n<p>-Maintains appropriate individual records documented in the SOAP format.</p>\n<p>-Demonstrates sound knowledge of clinical risk assessments and proactively ensures a safe environment during treatment of clients.</p>\n<p>-Work at all times within the scope of the workplace safety and health act of 2009 and Home policy for reporting of accidents, incidents, hazards and risk management.</p>\n<p>-Support or facilitate research initiatives with in Occupational therapy service.</p>\n<p>-Work with the multi-disciplinary team in intergrating the clients into the community.</p>\n<p>-Attend relevant meetings and give necessary input.</p>\n<p>-Undertake responsibility and duties assigned by the Director from time to time.</p>\n<p>Location:</p>\n<p>600  Upper Thomson Road S574421</p>",
